<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="194" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/2375.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">San José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s December 7 [4] and my December 7. I am told that Irias says
                            there should be no revolution; and that Irias and his colleagues have
                            “tied the hands of Mena.” Apparently their meeting in advance of Mena’s
                            arrival was to consider heading him off. * * *</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hale</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>